DOM

*DOM is the tree structure of html document.
*DOM is a application programming interface.
*by using dom we can easilt read, access and update contents in document.


3 different ways to access dom by using javascript

1.getElementById()
   - change contents by using its id name.
   -innerHTML:- to change the text contents
   -style:- to change the css property

2.getElementByClassName()
   -change contents by using class name.
   -we can give same class as multiple tags
   
3.getElentByTagName()
  -change contents by using its tag name.
  -you must give its index number to access the html element.

4.getElementByName()
  -change the content by using its name.
  -if have multiple no.of same name elements, you must give its index number.

5.getElementByCss selector()
  -access the dom elements by css selector
  -it have two choices:-
       *querySelector:-returns only one result
       *querySelectorAll:-returns multiple result

  -different css selectors are:-by idname,class and tag name.


  Event

  *to create an Event

  Event handler
    -an object can only one event handler

  Event Listener
    -we can add multiple event listeners at the same event.
    -it has 2 arguments:- event, function
    -event listener is a function. That function will trigger when a particular function is done.

  Event object
    -The argument of a function is called event object.
    